All,
  I am using Cantera in Matlab r2006b.
  I am having trouble with inputting my own cti files.
  I can't get my own cti files to read in. If I read in one of the pre-existing files, e.g., argon.cti,
  air.cti, h2o2.cti, etc., there is no problem.
  I even tried going in and modifying a copy of one of these, with even a minimal modification, for example changing: 
   
  ideal_gas(name = "ohmech"
   
  to:
   
  ideal_gas(name = "ohm"
   
  and the file cannot be read in.
   
  Here I copied h2o2.cti to h2o23.cti in the same directory (C:\Program Files\Common Files\Cantera\data\) and made the change. I run the following line and get the following errors. Can someone help?
   
  Many thanks,
  Ron Besser
   
  >> gas = importPhase('h2o23.cti','ohm')
???
